For expense report and supplier invoice transactions tied to a capital project worktag, Workday creates special accounting to appropriately debit the Work in Progress account, while also recording the amount as a debit into the Spend account.  This is necessary to reflect correct amounts for the purposes of Budget Checking/Reporting, and any other custom spend reports.

An expense report or supplier invoice line tied to a capital project transaction will create 4 lines.  First a debit to Spend, credit to Payables, then a debit to WIP and credit to Spend.  For budget checking/reporting, only the first debit to Spend should be captured, and the other credit to Spend excluded.  Additionally, if the transaction is reclassified to a Spend account from WIP, then 
the debit to Spend should also be excluded.  

Therefore, this boolean attribute is necessary to flag and identify the aforementioned Spend accounting lines that should not be included in Budget Checking/Reporting.

description: Returns the amount calculated from the award for a Facilities And Administration transaction in the Company currency. The calculated amount gets the effective rate for the effective award line for the effective award version where the effective date is the transaction's budget date. The effective rate is then multiplied by the spend paid amount.

fieldName: Facilities And Administration Amount from Award (Unpaid)

The calculated amount gets the effective rate for the effective award line for the effective award version where the effective date is the transaction's budget date. fieldName: Facilities And Administration Percentage from Award
description:
Returns the Facilities And Administration Percentage Rate that is from the effective award line where the budget date is the effective date. The rate is determined by the derived object class for the spend line.

The rate is obtained in the following order
a) Rate Override from Facilities And Administration Exception Detail matching Object Class
b) Primary Rate Override from Facilities And Administration Exception if Use Primary Rate = True (and no matching Object Class)
c) Rate from Cost Rate Type if above is false or No Exception defined on Award Contract Line
Returns the Facilities And Administration Percentage Posted that is calculated from the Facilities And Administration Amount Posted divided by the paid amount in Company Currency of the Spend Line.

fieldName: Facilities And Administration Posted Amount does not match Facilities And Administration Award Amount
description: Returns 'Yes' if the Facilities And Administration Posted Amount is Not Equal to the Facilities And Administration Award Amount for the spend line.
The Facilities And Administration Rate for the Object Class for the Award Line

fieldName: Facilities And Administration Rate for Award Line
description:
Returns the Facilities And Administration Percentage Rate from the Award Contract Line.

The rate determination does not use object class and will use an optional effective date if one is provided.

Workday obtains the rate using this order:

1) Primary Waive Rate Override from Facilities And Administration Exception, if Use Primary Waive Rate is true.
2) Primary Rate Override from Facilities And Administration Exception, if Use Primary Rate is true.
3) Rate from Cost Rate Type if the above are false, or if no Facilities And Administration Exception is defined on the Award Contract Line.
